   <pb facs="4"/>
   <head>To the Reader.</head>
   <p>
      <seg rend="decorInit">I</seg>T is the common custome to intreate fauour from courteous Readers: the cu<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>stome is not good, and ther<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>fore I vse it not; for if the matter merit, or the men bee courteous, the sute of fauour will bee easily granted; if o<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>therwise, it is but a needelesse shame to beg a commendation where it is not. And therefore I (willingly) leaue to euery man the liberty of his iudge<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ment, and expose this Tract to general censure.</p>
   <p>
      <hi>Faults escaped are corrected in the last Page.</hi>
   </p>
</div>
